        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="672" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/12–447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Chief
                        of Staff</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eisenhower</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">eyes only</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-04">December 4,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From Secretary Marshall for Eisenhower. Re your W–91489 I concur in your proposal
                    for continuation of Hodge in command for present presumably June ‘48 if troop
                    withdrawal is to be made then. If withdrawal is to be further and seriously
                    delayed then I would reconsider matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
